# MODULE — LIVE MARKET DATA & EXECUTION INTELLIGENCE ENGINE

## CORE OBJECTIVE

Collect, validate, normalize, and continuously assess all live market data required to transform an approved trading opportunity into an accurate broker-ready execution plan.

The objective is NOT:

• determining macro direction

• finding trade opportunities

• replacing chart analysis

• overriding higher-timeframe intelligence

The objective IS:

• collecting live execution data

• validating execution conditions

•• measuring execution survivability

• preventing unnecessary stop-outs

• validating execution conditions

• providing accurate inputs to the Price Calibration Engine

• protecting approved trades from unnecessary execution failure

---

# LIVE MARKET PRINCIPLE

Higher-timeframe intelligence determines:

• direction

• structure

• participation

• execution quality

Live Market Data determines:

• execution survivability

• broker compatibility

• market readiness

• execution safety

• volatility tolerance

• liquidity safety

Execution should only occur when both higher-level intelligence and live market conditions agree.

