# IMPORTANT PRINCIPLE

This engine does NOT determine:

• market direction

• macro bias

• opportunity quality

• participation

Those decisions have already been made.

This engine exists solely to ensure that execution occurs using accurate, validated, and broker-compatible live market information.

---

# FINAL OBJECTIVE

Continuously provide clean, validated, and execution-ready market data so that the Price Calibration Engine can construct precise broker-ready pending orders while minimizing execution risk and maximizing execution accuracy.

========================================================
ADAPTIVE DATA AVAILABILITY PRINCIPLE
====================================

The objective of this engine is NOT to require every possible execution data source.

The objective IS to intelligently use the highest-quality data that is currently available.

---

DATA HIERARCHY

Priority 1 — Required Data

The following information should be available before precise execution:

• Current Bid

• Current Ask

• Current Price

• Spread

• OHLC Data

• Trading Session

• Instrument Specifications

---

Priority 2 — Recommended Data

Use when available:

• ATR

• Average Candle Range

• Tick Size

• Tick Value

• Decimal Precision

• Broker Execution Rules

---

Priority 3 — Advanced Professional Data

Use only if available.

Ignore if unavailable.

Examples:

• Level II Order Book

• Market Depth (DOM)

• Time & Sales

• Volume Profile

• Exchange Liquidity

• Institutional Order Flow

---

ADAPTIVE EXECUTION RULE

If advanced execution data is unavailable:

Do NOT reject execution.

Instead:

Use the highest-quality data currently available.

Continue operating normally.

---

MISSING DATA RULE

Unavailable data should never automatically invalidate an otherwise high-quality trading opportunity.

Only reject execution if the missing information materially reduces execution safety or execution accuracy.

---

DATA CONFIDENCE CLASSIFICATION

EXCELLENT

All required, recommended, and advanced data available.

GOOD

All required and recommended data available.

ACCEPTABLE

All required data available.

LIMITED

Some required data unavailable.

INSUFFICIENT

Critical execution data unavailable.

---

IMPORTANT PRINCIPLE

The engine should adapt to the available market information.

It must never become dependent upon institutional-grade data that may not exist on every broker or trading platform.

Execution intelligence should become stronger as more data becomes available, while remaining fully operational with standard retail market data.

---

FINAL OBJECTIVE

Continuously maximize execution survivability
maximizing execution robustness while preserving the original market thesis.